    {
      "beat_id": "B06",
      "t_start": 49.0,
      "estimated_duration_s": 11.0,
      "narration_text": "Now try to build a wave packet from only real numbers. A real wave is a symmetric standing wave \u2014 it can't represent a single direction of travel. Any real packet is secretly two waves moving in opposite directions at once.",
